sentences: Ashton Nicole Casey (born February 19, 1996), known professionally as Ashnikko ( ash-NEE-koh), is an American singer and rapper.
She rose to prominence with her 2019 single "Stupid" with Yung Baby Tate, which gained viral popularity on the video-sharing platform TikTok and was certified gold in the United States and Canada.
Ashnikko's debut mixtape, Demidevil, was released in January 2021, and spawned the singles "Daisy" and "Slumber Party" featuring Princess Nokia.
Ashton Nicole Casey was born on February 19, 1996, in Oak Ridge, North Carolina, and raised in the city of Greensboro.

sentences: 2020–present: Breakthrough and Demidevil =
Prior to the COVID-19 pandemic, Ashnikko was scheduled to accompany Doja Cat on her Hot Pink Tour throughout the United States in March 2020 before it was cancelled.
In March 2020, she released the standalone single "Tantrum".
"Cry", featuring Canadian musician Grimes, was then released in June 2020, alongside an animated music video.
The song's music video was nominated for "Best Pop Video - UK" at the 2020 UK Music Video Awards.
Following this, "Daisy" was released in July 2020, and a music video for the song was released in collaboration with Beats by Dre and TikTok a month later.
Ashnikko's third Halloween song, "Halloweenie III: Seven Days", was released in October 2020.
She was nominated for Best Push Act at the 2020 MTV Europe Music Awards.
"Cry" and "Daisy" both appear on Ashnikko's debut mixtape, Demidevil, which was released on January 15, 2021.
In support of the mixtape, Ashnikko announced The Demidevil Tour, which is set to take place in October 2021, with shows in North America, the UK and Ireland.
In June 2019, Ashnikko stated on Twitter that she is bisexual.
In July 2020, while discussing the meaning behind the lyrics of her single "Daisy", she said that while her family practices Christianity, she does not.

In May 2021, Ashnikko came out as genderfluid on Twitter, saying that "i just didn't feel ready to tell the internet yet but i guess now's a good time since everyone's doing a dissection into my sexuality and gender identity".

She has been vocal about a range of social justice issues, having spoken out about the commercialization of feminism in November 2019, while advocating for victims of police brutality through social media.

In a 2020 interview, she clarified that she is pansexual.
She recalls becoming interested in music, specifically rap music, when she listened to Arular by M.I.A. at the age of 10, and says she did not listen to male musicians until she was 16 years old.
As a teenager, her family moved to Estonia for her father's studies, spending a year there before relocating again to Riga, Latvia.
She released the promotional single "Halloweenie II: Pumpkin Spice" in October 2019.
